Section Summary: The Bible contains passages that describe violent and vengeful acts, such as the destruction of cities and the slaughter of enemies, which may seem ferocious or egotistical. However, these passages must be considered in their historical context and within the ethical framework in which they were written. The concept of a Chosen People and other biblical ideas should be interpreted in relation to the time and circumstances in which they were written, rather than being judged by modern standards. It is also important to recognize that similar sentiments and desires for revenge can be found in modern times, even among non-Jews. Ultimately, understanding the Bible requires considering it within the broader context of human experience and nature, rather than isolating it from the world around it.
